osts of LGBTQ history. Together, they make the archive come alive in remarkably intimate ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchives in art. 0aDr. John P. De Cecco Archives and Research Center. 0aSexual minorities in art. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aart project, writing, LGBT writing, LGBT, queer culture, archives, history of LGBT, LGBT history, matching, individuals, LGBT individuals, Tina Takemoto, Luciano Chessa, Larry DeCaesar.1 aCrichton, E. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEscoffier, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Jonathan D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTea, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThinking, Magical, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVargas, Chris E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVargas, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882317440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978823174423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978823174/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023